cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

This paper deals with dense stereo matching, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses satellite images, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics) as well. The use of machine learning techniques and algorithms such as tMGM suggest that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and optimization, which could place it in cs.GR (Graphics).
